commentary: Starc to Stokes, OUT pretty full and on the stumps at 145ks, Stokes drives back to the bowler, who stretches his left hand and plucks it out. He has a aim at the stumps (sensing a run-out chance), Stokes, who is out of the crease, fends the throw off with his left glove/ instinctively looks to protect himself, as he loses his balance and collapses on the floor. Wade goes up. Starc appeals. Umpires Dharmasena and Robinson converge. The soft signal is not out. Stokes has been given out obstructing the field by the TV umpire Joe Wilson. Smith, Morgan intervene and have a chat with the umpires. Boos ring around Lord's. Morgan isn't happy. Stokes drags himself off the field. Roy, in the balcony, can't believe it. Drama! Drama!

commentary: Marsh to Morgan, SIX runs what an effort from NCN at the fine leg boundary. Good length on leg this time, Morgan clips the ball in the air with good timing. NCN takes a great catch and throws the ball back in at fine leg. NCN signals six to the umpire, but replays are inconclusive. Given six eventually.

commentary: Cummins to Morgan, OUT gone this time, that's the end of an amazing innings by Morgan and a really, good match. Australia win by 64 runs. Morgan and Smith have a chat while shaking hands. Good length outside off, Morgan looks to clear the long-off boundary with a heave but the ball lobs up nicely and sits in long-off's lap. Australia go 2-0 up in the five-match series.
